  ./COVERAGE.md:784:| `org.apache.camel:camel-jackson` | [4.20.0](metadata/org.apache.camel/camel-jackson/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Camel Jackson provides the JSON Jackson data format for marshalling Java objects to JSON and unmarshalling JSON back to Java objects in Camel routes. It also integrates Jackson with Camel type conversion and JSON data transformers so routes can exchange JSON, JsonNode, and POJO values.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.apache.camel/camel-jackson/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:909:| `org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson` | [1.12.2<br>- 1.15.2](metadata/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Parquet Jackson is the Parquet Java module that packages shaded Jackson libraries for use by Apache Parquet. It relocates Jackson classes under shaded.parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson so Parquet components can perform JSON serialization and parsing while avoiding dependency conflicts with applications.</details> | [100.0% (70/70 calls)](stats/org.apache.parquet/parquet-jackson/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:953:| `org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-core-asl` | [1.6.9<br>- 1.9.11](metadata/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-core-asl/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Jackson Core ASL 1.x provides the streaming JSON parser and generator APIs used by the original Jackson JSON processor. It lets Java applications read and write JSON content efficiently and forms the lower-level core used by Jackson's data-binding modules.</details> | [100.0% (1/1 calls)](stats/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-core-asl/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:954:| `org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-mapper-asl` | [1.8.3<br>- 1.9.13](metadata/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Jackson Mapper ASL 1.x provides the data-binding layer for the original Jackson JSON processor. It maps JSON to and from Java objects using ObjectMapper, serializers, deserializers, annotations, and type introspection built on jackson-core-asl.</details> | [100.0% (106/106 calls)](stats/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-mapper-asl/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:955:| `org.codehaus.jackson:jackson-xc` | [1.8.3<br>- 1.8.4](metadata/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-xc/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Jackson XC adds XML-compatibility extensions to Jackson 1.x data binding, including support for JAXB annotations and XML-related Java types when serializing and deserializing JSON. It lets applications reuse JAXB metadata with Jackson's mapper for JSON interoperability rather than performing XML processing itself.</details> | [100.0% (4/4 calls)](stats/org.codehaus.jackson/jackson-xc/) |
