etadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jaxrs/jackson-jaxrs-base/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"jackson-jaxrs-base provides the shared base classes, configuration helpers, annotations, and utilities used by Jackson's JAX-RS message body providers. It supports Jackson-based integration with JAX-RS providers for serializing and deserializing request and response bodies across supported data formats.\",\n./metadata/io.fabric8/kubernetes-model-common/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Fabric8 Kubernetes Model Common provides shared Java model annotations, builder APIs, and Jackson helpers used by the Fabric8 Kubernetes and OpenShift model artifacts. It supports representing and serializing Kubernetes resource model classes consistently across the Fabric8 Kubernetes Client ecosystem.\",\n./metadata/io.fabric8/zjsonpatch/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"zjsonpatch is Fabric8's Java library for applying RFC 6902 JSON Patch operations and generating diffs between Jackson JsonNode trees. It supports patch application, diff generation, and JSON Pointer path handling for JSON documents in JVM applications.\",\n./tests/src/org.playframework/play-json_3/3.0.0/src/test/scala/org_playframework/play_json_3/Play_json_3Test.scala:153:      \"name\" -> \"Mary Jackson\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Dataformat CBOR adds support for reading and writing Concise Binary Object Representation (CBOR) data through Jackson's streaming, data binding, and tree model APIs. It provides CBOR-specific parser, generator, factory, and mapper implementations so Java applications can serialize and deserialize objects and JSON-like structures in a compact binary format.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-toml/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Dataformat TOML adds Jackson support for reading and writing TOML documents. It provides TOML parsing and generation through Jackson's streaming and databinding APIs.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-yaml/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Dataformat YAML provides Jackson-backed reading and writing of YAML data through the standard streaming and data-binding APIs. It integrates SnakeYAML as the underlying YAML parser and generator so Java applications can serialize and deserialize YAML alongside other Jackson data formats.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs/jackson-jakarta-rs-yaml-provider/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jakarta-RS YAML Provider integrates Jackson data binding with Jakarta RESTful Web Services implementations to read and write YAML request and response bodies. It supplies YAML MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter providers, including JAXB-annotation-aware support, for frameworks such as Jersey and RESTEasy.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs/jackson-jakarta-rs-yaml-provider/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jakarta-RS YAML Provider integrates Jackson data binding with Jakarta RESTful Web Services implementations to read and write YAML request and response bodies. It supplies YAML MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter providers, including JAXB-annotation-aware support, for frameworks such as Jersey and RESTEasy.\",\n./stats/tools.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/3.1.0/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/tools.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/3.1.0/src/test/java/tools_jackson_dataformat/jackson_dataformat_cbor/Jackson_dataformat_cborTest.java\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs/jackson-jakarta-rs-json-provider/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jakarta-RS JSON Provider integrates Jackson data binding with Jakarta RESTful Web Services implementations to read and write JSON request and response bodies. It supplies JSON MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter providers, automatic provider registration, and Jackson-specific configuration support for REST endpoints.\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs/jackson-jakarta-rs-json-provider/index.json:23:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jakarta-RS JSON Provider supplies MessageBodyReader and MessageBodyWriter implementations that let Jakarta-RS runtimes read and write JSON through Jackson data binding. It supports automatic provider registration and Jackson-specific configuration annotations for JSON endpoints.\",\n./stats/tools.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-yaml/3.1.0/execution-metrics.json:52:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/tools.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-yaml/3.1.0/src/test/java/tools_jackson_dataformat/jackson_dataformat_yaml/Jackson_dataformat_yamlTest.java\",\n./metadata/com.fasterxml.jackson.jakarta.rs/jackson-jakarta-rs-base/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Jackson Jakarta RS Base contains shared support code used by Jackson's Jakarta RESTful Web Services providers. It supplies common annotations, configuration, provider base classes, and utilities that integrate Jackson data binding with Jakarta WS RS runtime implementations.\",\n./metadata/org.springframework/spring-context/6.0.0/reachability-metadata.json:923:      \"type\" : \"org.springframework.http.converter.json.JacksonModulesRuntimeHints\",\n./stats/tools.jackson.core/jackson-databind/3.0.0/execution-metrics.json:58:      \"test_file\" : \"tests/src/tools.jackson.core/jackson-databind/3.0.0/src/test/java/tools_jackson_core/jackson_databind/Jackson_databindTest.java\",\n./tests/src/com.alibaba/fastjson/1.2.83/src/test/java/com_alibaba/fastjson/ParserConfigTest.java:52:        creatorConfig.setJacksonCompatible(true);\n./metadata/com.github.java-json-tools/json-patch/index.json:9:    \"description\": \"json-patch implements JSON Patch (RFC 6902) and JSON Merge Patch (RFC 7386) for Java applications. It provides Jackson-based operations for applying, representing, and validating JSON document changes.\",\n./metadata/com.github.java-json-tools/jac